title: For Sale:  Daniel Defense 300 Blackout Ambush
postcontent:
This is an awesome Daniel Defense Ambush rifle chambered in 300 Blackout.  I've put about 200 rounds through the rifle and the BCG is BRAND NEW (CMMG) with zero rounds through it.  

The Ambush has a Magpul 6 position MOE stock with the extended buttplate for even better recoil reduction.  It also has an adjustable bipod on the front picatinny rail.  There is a free floating modular rail along the entire top of the rifle, as well as user adjustable rails at 3, 6, and 9 o'clock for any accessories. The Ambush also has a use adjustable shotgun inspired handgrip, which can easily be replaced by any kind of hand guard or other accessories you like.

The Cold hammer forged 16" barrel has a 1:8 twist and is threaded for any muzzle brake/suppressor accessories you would like.  It comes with a standard flash suppressor already attached, and can easily be changed out with whatever you would like.  It is a Carbine length gas system, with a mil-spec upper/lower and a salt bath nitride finish.  

The lower is the exact same lower as any AR-15 style 223/5.56 rifle and uses the same magazine! So you can use this rifle's lower for any 223/5.56 uppers you have and swap back and forth between calibers at your leisure.

All in all, this is an absolutely amazing rifle. It is extremely high quality and will be able to stand up to any test.  

The bipod shown in the pictures IS included with the rifle, as is 1 standard GI 30 round magazine and hard case.  

If you would like any other pictures, or if you live in the area and want to see the rifle in person please let me know.  I am open to any offers, so if you are at all interested please don't hesitate to contact me!

title: For Sale:  Beretta CX-4 9mm Excellent Condition w/ Extras
postcontent:
This Beretta CX-4 9mm really is in excellent condition. It has been lightly used and well taken care of. I love this gun and makes an excellent home defense gun but I'm looking to get into some long range shooting and I need the cash.

Extras:
Comes with 3 - 30 round Beretta factory magazines ($120 Value if you can get them) and 2 - 15 round Beretta magazines (it takes the same magazine as the 92).
Also Includes 20mm Red Dot Sight. 

From Beretta:
CX4 Storm: A Tactical Carbine with Pistol-Like Controls

The CX4 is a semiauto pistol-caliber carbine designed to give you the familiar controls of your favorite Beretta combat handgun. It is perfect for shooters who are already familiar with Beretta tactical pistols, or more in general for those who may not have extensive experience with a rifle or carbine. However, the cold-hammer forged barrel delivers the sort of accuracy that even the most experienced shooters will appreciate. Easy to use, ultra-reliable and low-recoil, it has been adopted by several police agencies aross the US, while its versatility and accessorization options have made it a favorite of recreational shooters. Whether you use it for home-defense, varminting, competition or training, the CX4 will deliver what it promises.

Accepts Beretta Full-Size Pistol Magazines

The CX4 is adaptable to accept any full-size Beretta PX4, 90-series and 8000 series magazines (using optional adapters), thereby saving existing Beretta users the expense of additional magazines. Along with its uncompromising Beretta quality, this is an additional reason why the versatility of this carbine is highly prized by tactical shooters. Along with a Beretta pistol, it helps create the best and most versatile tactical system available today, as evidenced by the CX4’s dedicated following.

cx4-1Extremely Versatile, Easy to Use

This light and compact carbine was designed to be completely and easily adaptable to the needs of most shooters. The operating handle, safety and magazine release are reversible and give you the opportunity to train or shoot right- or left-handed, while case ejection can also be switched from right to left. The length of pull is adjustable (one spacer included), making the CX4 easily and intuitively come up to the shoulder of most shooters. The aperture and post sights are user-adjustable, meaning that you can train with (or switch) your favorite brand of ammo without taking the carbine to a gunsmith. And after a day at the range, this carbine is a snap to take apart and reassemble, while its ultra-tough construction and surface treatment make it stand up to the hardest use.

Easy Accessorization

The CX4 jsut begs to be accessorized. Between the front and rear sights, it features a full-length aluminum top rail for mounting optical and red dot sights. It also sports a retractable Picatinny rail that extends from the fore-end, which allows users to mount tactical lighting devices and other accessories. Additional rails can be mounted on the left, right and bottom, thereby providing ample opportunity for customization. Please visit our accessories page for a full list of CX4 accessories.   

Sorry, no trades unless you have something in 6.5 Grendel you are willing to part with.

title: For Sale:  SCAM ALERT!!!  Beware of Springfield EMP from Boscobel below!!!!!
postcontent: This guy wasted weeks of my time!  First he wanted to trade for a P229R, I had a pristine one for sale or trade (still do on here) and contacted him.  He was all for it, then got cold feet and had to "research" them. Lo and behold, turns out he thinks Sig P229s all suck and doesn't want to trade.  So then he relists it for sale only and I contact him again.  He says we may be able to meet in Madison if we are really serious about buying it, I am so we take him up on that offer, suddenly he has no transportation because he is wheelchair bound and his sons car broke down.  I then offer to pay him his full asking price and drive to Boscobel to buy it and he disappears!!!!  no more contact for a few days.  Then he tells me he went to Prairie Du Chien with family (remember, he is house bound and his ONLY source of transport does not work)  He also tells me that his son has expressed interest and wants the gun so he is not selling it anymore.  A week later he reposts it now!!  He is more than likely a shut in just looking for attention.  He will waste your time and not sell you his gun!!!!!!!!!!!!  I told him that was my opinion and he did not dispute it.

title: For Sale:  Mil-spec Panasonic Toughbook CF-29
postcontent:
This laptop and I have some history; in 6+ years on duty it’s gone everywhere I did (every computer killing place the military sent me), but you can’t tell by looking at it. It’s survived the woods of Virginia, the desert in Nevada, the swamp in Louisiana, the weeds in Texas, and even the jungle in Guatemala. It’s been through rain, thunder, and dust storms, even a blizzard. I’m not sure it’ll work as a SAPI plate, but I can say nothing else short of deflecting bullets has killed it. It was never meant to be the fastest, lightest, or prettiest thing in the world, but when a lot of the other guys’ widescreen hotrods started  crapping out as soon as it got hot or cold or wet or dry, this little beast has ALWAYS worked. It has gotten a few scratches, but everything works and even all the port covers are intact in spite of all the backpacks, Blackhawks, and Hum-Vees it’s been bounced around in.

Listing includes one each mil-spec, fully-rugged Panasonic Toughbook CF-29 notebook computer with 1.6 GHz Intel processor, upgraded 1.25 Gb RAM (256Kb onboard), upgraded 160 Gb hard drive (130 Gb free for manuals, movies, or MP3’s), upgraded DVD/CD-RW ROM drive, upgraded back-lit rubberized keyboard (has survived several MRE coffee baths, and original tactile keyboard included), and built-in Wi-Fi. Running Windows XP Professional, with Microsoft Plus! for XP, Microsoft Security Essentials, and full Microsoft Office 2007. Possible additional upgrades/add-on’s include touch screen and/or GPS, and supposedly Win 7, but those are up to you.

I’m pretty much done traveling, but if you want a hunting/camping, field-duty/ bug-out, work-truck dependable, zombie-proof computer, this is it. Price includes laptop, OEM power brick, and power cord only; military transport, covert missions, crappy weather, and apocalyptic situations not issued/supplied.

Email or call/text 5-oh-5 seven-1-two 5-one-3-four Thanks!

PS. I also have a portable Canon iP90 printer and some travel speakers to go with this listed separately and if you're wanting a faster system just not quite as tough, I also have a CF-74 listed.
